1
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:49,260
Speaker 1: You're just staring at the moon and smiling You're so absorbed in searching for something to gently touch Your eyes are so painful,

2
00:02:12,740 --> 00:02:16,280
Shinji: He was still an angel! He was still one of the enemy!

3
00:02:17,800 --> 00:02:20,340
Shinji: He wasn't! He wasn't! He wasn't!

4
00:02:21,480 --> 00:02:23,300
Rei: Even though he was as human as me?

5
00:02:24,060 --> 00:02:25,540
Shinji: No! He was an angel!

6
00:02:26,400 --> 00:02:27,760
Rei: Is that why you killed him?

7
00:02:28,260 --> 00:02:32,160
Shinji: Yes! Otherwise we'd all die! We'd have all been destroyed!

8
00:02:32,840 --> 00:02:34,160
Rei: So that's why you killed him?

9
00:02:34,540 --> 00:02:37,580
Shinji: I didn't want to kill him! I didn't have a choice!

10
00:02:38,740 --> 00:02:43,120
Shinji: Help me! Please, just help me!

11
00:02:43,550 --> 00:02:45,040
Shinji: For God's sake, help me!

12
00:02:46,300 --> 00:02:47,660
Shinji: Somebody please help me!

13
00:02:48,300 --> 00:02:50,840
Shinji: Is anyone listening? Somebody please help me!

14
00:02:56,880 --> 00:02:58,380
Shinji: He was much better than I am.

15
00:02:59,780 --> 00:03:01,120
Shinji: Karu should have survived.

16
00:03:01,560 --> 00:03:02,680
Shinji: Not me.

17
00:03:03,820 --> 00:03:08,040
Misato: No. The one who deserves to survive is the one who has the will to make it happen.

18
00:03:09,440 --> 00:03:10,920
Misato: He wished for death.

19
00:03:12,360 --> 00:03:16,340
Misato: He ignored his will to survive and chose to die for a false hope.

20
00:03:17,780 --> 00:03:19,680
Misato: Survival is not a mistake, Shinji.

21
00:03:20,040 --> 00:03:20,600
Shinji: Are you sure?

22
00:03:21,640 --> 00:03:22,860
Shinji: Are you sure it was right?

23
00:03:24,080 --> 00:03:25,380
Shinji: I don't understand.

24
00:03:26,240 --> 00:03:27,160
Shinji: What can I do?

25
00:03:27,920 --> 00:03:29,120
Shinji: What am I supposed to do?

26
00:03:30,520 --> 00:03:31,220
Shinji: What was that?

27
00:03:32,360 --> 00:03:33,160
Shinji: I fear myself?

28
00:03:34,260 --> 00:03:35,260
Shinji: I fear being hated?

29
00:03:36,500 --> 00:03:37,460
Shinji: But by whom?

30
00:03:37,460 --> 00:03:39,740
Shinji: Who is it? It's my...

31
00:03:40,440 --> 00:03:40,780
Shinji: Father.

32
00:03:42,020 --> 00:03:44,160
Shinji: My father abandoned me. He hates me!

33
00:03:45,760 --> 00:03:47,900
Shinji: If others hate me, what will I do?

34
00:03:48,200 --> 00:03:49,260
Shinji: What will I do?

35
00:04:00,220 --> 00:04:01,220
Shinji: Where am I?

36
00:04:02,019 --> 00:04:04,160
Shinji: Where am I supposed to go?

37
00:04:04,440 --> 00:04:05,720
Shinji: I can't see anything.

38
00:04:05,720 --> 00:04:07,580
Shinji: I don't understand what I feel.

39
00:04:10,500 --> 00:04:13,260
Shinji: Misato? Misato!

40
00:04:14,680 --> 00:04:17,640
Shinji: Hey! Where are you, Misato? I can't see!

41
00:04:18,660 --> 00:04:20,320
Shinji: Hey, where am I supposed to go?

42
00:04:22,740 --> 00:04:29,580
Shinji: Misato? Asuka? Ayanami? Toji? Kitsuke? Ritsuko? Kaji?

43
00:04:30,720 --> 00:04:30,920
Shinji: Father!

44
00:04:32,660 --> 00:04:33,220
Shinji: Mother...

45
00:04:34,760 --> 00:04:36,940
Shinji: Somebody please tell me what I have to do now!

46
00:04:38,600 --> 00:04:39,160
Shinji: Eva...

47
00:04:40,780 --> 00:04:42,960
Shinji: Evangelion Unit 1...

48
00:04:44,660 --> 00:04:46,200
Shinji: I still have to pilot it?

49
00:04:46,700 --> 00:04:48,040
Shinji: Even after it made me kill him?

50
00:04:49,140 --> 00:04:53,420
Shinji: My father and the others tell me that I have to pilot it no matter what I want!

51
00:04:53,760 --> 00:04:56,080
Shinji: Why do I have to keep fighting after all that's happened?

52
00:04:56,520 --> 00:04:58,160
Shinji: Mother! Say something!

53
00:04:59,040 --> 00:04:59,520
Shinji: Answer me!

54
00:05:02,160 --> 00:05:03,880
Shinji: Because everyone tells me to.

55
00:05:05,060 --> 00:05:06,000
Shinji: What do you mean?

56
00:05:06,500 --> 00:05:07,780
Shinji: It's for the sake of mankind.

57
00:05:08,420 --> 00:05:09,320
Shinji: Isn't that good enough?

58
00:05:10,880 --> 00:05:11,680
Shinji: That's right!

59
00:05:12,300 --> 00:05:13,840
Shinji: Is there something wrong with that?

60
00:05:14,260 --> 00:05:15,640
Shinji: I'm doing the right thing!

61
00:05:16,300 --> 00:05:18,540
Shinji: And when I do it, the others appreciate me!

62
00:05:18,900 --> 00:05:20,300
Shinji: The others like me then!

63
00:05:20,440 --> 00:05:21,320
Asuka: You're lying!

64
00:05:22,340 --> 00:05:23,680
Asuka: Are you stupid?

65
00:05:24,050 --> 00:05:26,520
Asuka: You know damn well that you do this for yourself.

66
00:05:27,720 --> 00:05:30,660
Asuka: You're just making up excuses like you always do.

67
00:05:31,300 --> 00:05:31,840
Shinji: I do?

68
00:05:32,800 --> 00:05:35,960
Asuka: Pretending you're sacrificing yourself is just another cop-out.

69
00:05:36,350 --> 00:05:38,880
Asuka: It makes you feel so special to play the martyr.

70
00:05:38,900 --> 00:05:40,160
Shinji: I'm not sure that's true.

71
00:05:40,580 --> 00:05:43,460
Asuka: You're feeling lonely and isolated, nothing more.

72
00:05:43,900 --> 00:05:44,360
Shinji: Am I?

73
00:05:45,400 --> 00:05:46,540
Asuka: Of course you are!

74
00:05:46,750 --> 00:05:49,960
Asuka: You live on sympathy and you get it with your Eva, Shinji!

75
00:05:50,280 --> 00:05:51,000
Shinji: It could be true.

76
00:05:51,520 --> 00:05:53,620
Asuka: You love having others depend upon you.

77
00:05:54,080 --> 00:05:56,540
Asuka: It satisfies your twisted little mind.

78
00:05:56,540 --> 00:05:57,960
Shinji: That could be...

79
00:05:59,140 --> 00:06:05,000
Asuka: If you want real happiness, you've got to find it for yourself, not wait for someone to give it to you!

80
00:06:05,800 --> 00:06:07,320
Rei: But isn't that what you've been doing?

81
00:06:17,600 --> 00:06:19,520
Asuka: I didn't want to be in this thing again.

82
00:06:20,080 --> 00:06:21,840
Asuka: They're forcing me to pilot this.

83
00:06:22,700 --> 00:06:24,920
Asuka: But this piece of junk won't work.

84
00:06:25,540 --> 00:06:28,300
Asuka: But it's only junk because of what I've become.

85
00:06:29,320 --> 00:06:30,340
Asuka: I'm the garbage now.

86
00:06:31,560 --> 00:06:32,280
Asuka: I'm worthless.

87
00:06:33,160 --> 00:06:34,300
Asuka: Nobody needs me.

88
00:06:36,060 --> 00:06:39,240
Asuka: But he needs a pilot who can't even control her own Eva.

89
00:06:40,700 --> 00:06:43,340
Rei: You seek your own value in the perception of others.

90
00:06:43,780 --> 00:06:44,680
Asuka: Shut up!

91
00:06:46,040 --> 00:06:47,400
Rei: Do you fear being loved?

92
00:06:48,120 --> 00:06:49,000
Rei: Do you fear being...

93
00:06:49,000 --> 00:06:51,840
Rei: Are you afraid that you will lose your identity if others leave you?

94
00:06:52,640 --> 00:06:54,760
Young Asuka: You pilot Eva so you'll be praised.

95
00:06:54,760 --> 00:06:58,380
Asuka: Shut up! Shut up! Leave me alone!

96
00:06:58,740 --> 00:07:01,820
Asuka: How can a wind-up doll like you dare tell me that?!

97
00:07:05,380 --> 00:07:06,280
Rei: Who am I?

98
00:07:06,640 --> 00:07:07,660
Rei: You are Rei Ayanami.

99
00:07:08,400 --> 00:07:09,980
Rei: But who are you?

100
00:07:11,780 --> 00:07:13,520
Rei: Are you Rei Ayanami as well?

101
00:07:13,940 --> 00:07:17,020
Rei: Correct. I'm the thing that is recognized as Rei Ayanami.

102
00:07:17,380 --> 00:07:20,340
Young Rei: We are all things that are recognized as Rei Ayanami.

103
00:07:20,820 --> 00:07:22,740
Rei: How could all of those possibly be me?

104
00:07:23,160 --> 00:07:25,940
Rei: It is simply because the others call us Rei Ayanami.

105
00:07:26,340 --> 00:07:27,380
Rei: That is the only reason.

106
00:07:28,000 --> 00:07:30,640
Young Rei: You possess a false body and a fake soul.

107
00:07:30,890 --> 00:07:31,820
Young Rei: Do you know why?

108
00:07:32,220 --> 00:07:33,980
Rei: I am neither false nor fake.

109
00:07:34,140 --> 00:07:35,160
Rei: I am simply me.

110
00:07:35,800 --> 00:07:36,180
Rei: No.

111
00:07:36,830 --> 00:07:41,480
Rei: You are an empty shell with a false soul, created by a man named Gendo Ikari.

112
00:07:42,140 --> 00:07:44,740
Rei: You are just an object that is pretending to be a human.

113
00:07:45,280 --> 00:07:46,520
Rei: Look deep within yourself.

114
00:07:47,150 --> 00:07:52,000
Rei: Do you perceive the almost intangible and invisible presence that lurks below your waking self?

115
00:07:52,000 --> 00:07:57,200
Rei: Inside your darkest dreams, It is there that your true identity lies.

116
00:07:57,700 --> 00:07:58,920
Rei: No, I am me.

117
00:07:59,600 --> 00:08:05,280
Rei: I became myself by the instrumentality of the links and relationships between myself and others.

118
00:08:06,140 --> 00:08:08,400
Rei: I am formed by interaction with others.

119
00:08:09,020 --> 00:08:10,560
Rei: They create me as I create them.

120
00:08:11,220 --> 00:08:15,780
Rei: These relationships and interactions serve to shape the patterns of my heart and mind.

121
00:08:17,520 --> 00:08:22,640
Rei: Yes, that is the name for what I share with those who have created the thing known as Rei.

122
00:08:23,160 --> 00:08:25,320
Rei: That is what will continue to shape me.

123
00:08:27,100 --> 00:08:29,700
Young Rei: But there is someone else who is your true self.

124
00:08:30,950 --> 00:08:33,280
Young Rei: You don't know her, but she exists.

125
00:08:34,110 --> 00:08:38,120
Young Rei: You deny that fact in attempt to suppress that facet of your reality.

126
00:08:39,500 --> 00:08:41,419
Young Rei: Because she might not have human form.

127
00:08:42,700 --> 00:08:45,140
Young Rei: Because then the present self might cease to be.

128
00:08:46,240 --> 00:08:49,740
Young Rei: This is what you fear, that you will become nothing.

129
00:08:50,920 --> 00:08:54,500
Young Rei: You are frightened that you will disappear from the minds of others if another exists.

130
00:08:54,900 --> 00:08:55,540
Rei: I'm afraid.

131
00:08:56,250 --> 00:08:57,080
Rei: Why is that?

132
00:08:57,660 --> 00:09:00,060
Rei: Because your current self will have never existed.

133
00:09:00,660 --> 00:09:04,380
Rei: Because you will cease to be.

134
00:09:05,200 --> 00:09:06,480
Rei: No, I'm not.

135
00:09:07,300 --> 00:09:08,140
Rei: I am happy.

136
00:09:09,720 --> 00:09:11,100
Rei: Because I want to die.

137
00:09:12,120 --> 00:09:13,080
Rei: I want despair.

138
00:09:14,240 --> 00:09:17,840
Rei: I want to return to nothing, but I can't.

139
00:09:18,400 --> 00:09:20,260
Rei: He won't let me return to nothing.

140
00:09:20,440 --> 00:09:22,440
Rei: There's nothing. There's nothing.

141
00:09:22,940 --> 00:09:25,360
Rei: I still exist because he needs me.

142
00:09:26,640 --> 00:09:32,280
Rei: But when everything is over, when I am of no use anymore, he will abandon me.

143
00:09:33,700 --> 00:09:39,360
Rei: I've prayed for the day he would abandon me, but now, now I fear it.

144
00:09:42,240 --> 00:09:48,900
Gendo: Come, let us go. This is the day for which you were created, Rei.

145
00:09:49,920 --> 00:09:50,320
Rei: Yes, sir.

146
00:10:02,079 --> 00:10:08,260
Shinji: What? What feeling is this? I think I've experienced this sensation before.

147
00:10:09,240 --> 00:10:11,820
Shinji: It's as though my physical form was disappearing.

148
00:10:12,999 --> 00:10:14,440
Shinji: It feels... agreeable.

149
00:10:15,040 --> 00:10:18,760
Shinji: As though my existence is spreading itself out to cover the entirety of existence.

150
00:10:32,440 --> 00:10:34,960
Gendo: Incorrect. It is not a return to nothingness.

151
00:10:35,370 --> 00:10:37,640
Gendo: It is merely a return to a state of beginning.

152
00:10:38,240 --> 00:10:41,980
Gendo: It is no less than a return to the primal womb that we lost so long ago.

153
00:10:42,720 --> 00:10:45,640
Gendo: Souls and minds will become one, attaining eternal balance.

154
00:10:45,980 --> 00:10:48,020
Gendo: The final goal is nothing more than that.

155
00:10:48,440 --> 00:10:49,600
Misato: And that's instrumentality?

156
00:10:50,120 --> 00:10:53,220
Ritsuko: Yes. There is an emptiness at the very core of our souls.

157
00:10:54,080 --> 00:10:57,980
Ritsuko: A fundamental incompleteness that has haunted all beings since the very first thought.

158
00:10:58,400 --> 00:11:03,060
Ritsuko: On a primal level, man has always been aware of the darkness that resides at the core of his mind.

159
00:11:03,540 --> 00:11:09,240
Ritsuko: We have seeked to escape from this void and the fear it causes, and all man's accomplishments were made in the hope of filling it.

160
00:11:09,380 --> 00:11:12,140
Misato: And so you'll just crush everyone's minds together to fill the gaps?

161
00:11:12,640 --> 00:11:14,320
Misato: Who made you humanity's overseer?

162
00:11:14,600 --> 00:11:19,140
Misato: You came to us bearing an offer of help, yet your benevolence has proved to be as false as our friendship!

163
00:11:19,200 --> 00:11:21,780
Ritsuko: And yet that is exactly as you wished it to be!

164
00:11:23,900 --> 00:11:24,680
Misato: Where am I?

165
00:11:28,520 --> 00:11:30,960
Shinji: This is the me that exists in your mind, Misato.

166
00:11:31,720 --> 00:11:35,860
Misato: And yet at the same time, this is also the me which exists in your mind, isn't it Shinji?

167
00:11:35,860 --> 00:11:40,680
Shinji: In order to establish my identity, I have to communicate with the minds of many people.

168
00:11:40,920 --> 00:11:43,280
Shinji: I have to examine that which is at my core.

169
00:11:43,640 --> 00:11:47,140
Shinji: I have to stare at Misato, who resides on the inside of my mind.

170
00:11:47,660 --> 00:11:49,060
Shinji: What is it that you wish for, Misato?

171
00:11:50,940 --> 00:11:52,460
Young Misato: I have to be a good child.

172
00:11:54,100 --> 00:11:55,360
Young Misato: Because I have no daddy.

173
00:11:56,080 --> 00:11:58,100
Young Misato: Because I have to be good and not bother my mommy.

174
00:11:59,360 --> 00:12:01,140
Young Misato: But I don't want to become like my mom.

175
00:12:01,540 --> 00:12:03,440
Young Misato: When my father is not here, she always cries.

176
00:12:03,860 --> 00:12:06,940
Young Misato: I can't cry. I can't depend on anyone else.

177
00:12:07,520 --> 00:12:08,420
Young Misato: So I have to be good.

178
00:12:08,740 --> 00:12:10,800
Young Misato: That way maybe my father won't hate me as much.

179
00:12:11,320 --> 00:12:14,260
Young Misato: I hope. Maybe my father won't hate me if I be good.

180
00:12:14,320 --> 00:12:15,420
Misato: But I hated my father.

181
00:12:16,320 --> 00:12:17,880
Misato: And I hated being a good child.

182
00:12:18,880 --> 00:12:19,480
Misato: I hate it.

183
00:12:20,360 --> 00:12:21,520
Misato: I'm tired of it.

184
00:12:21,700 --> 00:12:23,860
Misato: I'm tired of keeping myself clean.

185
00:12:24,260 --> 00:12:26,700
Misato: I'm tired of pretending to be pure and noble.

186
00:12:27,220 --> 00:12:28,600
Misato: I'm so tired of it all.

187
00:12:28,860 --> 00:12:32,320
Misato: I want to disgrace myself to get so dirty that no one can stand it.

188
00:12:32,320 --> 00:12:34,600
Misato: I'd want to see my life and my reputation ruined.

189
00:12:34,980 --> 00:12:37,320
Ritsuko: Is that why you slept with him? With Kaji?

190
00:12:37,820 --> 00:12:40,020
Misato: No! I slept with him because I love him!

191
00:12:40,460 --> 00:12:43,280
Young Misato: You did? Did you really love him?

192
00:12:43,460 --> 00:12:46,900
Misato: Yes, I did! He accepted me as myself, for the real me!

193
00:12:48,500 --> 00:12:50,060
Misato: That's why I let him make love to me!

194
00:12:50,820 --> 00:12:51,260
Maya: (dramatic music)

195
00:13:03,220 --> 00:13:04,920
Misato: - No, don't show Shinji this.

196
00:13:04,980 --> 00:13:06,680
Misato: I don't want him to see that side of me.

197
00:13:07,620 --> 00:13:10,120
Kaji: - Why are you still embarrassed after all that's happened?

198
00:13:10,620 --> 00:13:12,280
Misato: - Because I'm ashamed of it.

199
00:13:12,720 --> 00:13:13,980
Misato: - Why does this embarrass you?

200
00:13:14,100 --> 00:13:15,040
Misato: You weren't ashamed then.

201
00:13:15,220 --> 00:13:17,600
Misato: You were glad to show your true nature to the man you loved.

202
00:13:17,780 --> 00:13:19,440
Misato: In fact, you took great pleasure in it.

203
00:13:19,840 --> 00:13:20,960
Misato: No, don't do this!

204
00:13:22,100 --> 00:13:23,720
Misato: You wanted to dirty yourself?

205
00:13:24,080 --> 00:13:27,120
Misato: You should be happy to show this side of yourself to Shinji, shouldn't you?

206
00:13:27,180 --> 00:13:28,700
Misato: No! No, no!

207
00:13:29,840 --> 00:13:30,700
Misato: Are you sure?

208
00:13:31,360 --> 00:13:33,660
Misato: Or is it perhaps your father that you'd like to show this to?

209
00:13:33,900 --> 00:13:34,360
Misato: No!

210
00:13:35,580 --> 00:13:38,680
Misato: Wasn't it really peace of mind that you were seeking in Kaji's bed?

211
00:13:38,860 --> 00:13:39,400
Misato: No!

212
00:13:40,340 --> 00:13:42,820
Misato: You wanted peace of mind and warmth from Kaji then?

213
00:13:43,480 --> 00:13:43,920
Misato: No!

214
00:13:44,220 --> 00:13:47,640
Misato: You wanted to find your father in Kaji's embrace, didn't you?

215
00:13:48,000 --> 00:13:48,820
Rei: It's not true!

216
00:13:49,480 --> 00:13:52,800
Misato: It is true. In Kaji, I'd found my father reborn.

217
00:13:54,020 --> 00:13:56,720
Misato: And so I fled from him. I was so afraid.

218
00:13:57,640 --> 00:13:59,160
Misato: He was so much like my father.

219
00:14:00,460 --> 00:14:02,560
Misato: But at the same time, I was also very happy.

220
00:14:03,760 --> 00:14:04,660
Misato: I was never happier.

221
00:14:05,960 --> 00:14:07,500
Misato: That was such a wonderful time.

222
00:14:08,980 --> 00:14:09,840
Misato: That's why I hated it.

223
00:14:11,220 --> 00:14:12,040
Misato: That's why I left.

224
00:14:13,820 --> 00:14:14,980
Misato: That's why I ran away.

225
00:14:19,080 --> 00:14:24,080
Kaji: So, no reason was required to begin our love, but you needed a reason for ending it.

226
00:14:24,740 --> 00:14:26,840
Misato: Yes, you were so kind, Kaji.

227
00:14:28,320 --> 00:14:34,140
Misato: You were so kind to disgrace me, to dirty me, to deflower me.

228
00:14:37,200 --> 00:14:40,680
Kaji: Just because you hate yourself is no reason to injure yourself further.

229
00:14:41,640 --> 00:14:45,360
Kaji: Punishing yourself is simply a cheat to make you feel better for a little while.

230
00:14:46,720 --> 00:14:47,720
Kaji: Don't do this to yourself.

231
00:14:48,580 --> 00:14:50,280
Misato: Now you'll tell me to take care of myself?

232
00:14:51,660 --> 00:14:52,660
Misato: Men always do that.

233
00:14:53,540 --> 00:14:57,700
Misato: They'll escape to their jobs, their own world, and leave me behind.

234
00:14:58,590 --> 00:15:00,180
Misato: They always leave me behind.

235
00:15:01,340 --> 00:15:03,300
Young Misato: Always. Just like our father did.

236
00:15:04,760 --> 00:15:07,000
Misato: They always escape from the harsh realities.

237
00:15:08,400 --> 00:15:09,260
Misato: Harsh reality.

238
00:15:10,680 --> 00:15:11,960
Misato: I am his harsh reality.

239
00:15:13,500 --> 00:15:16,460
Misato: Of course, I am the problem.

240
00:15:16,580 --> 00:15:18,200
Shinji: Stop this! Misato!

241
00:15:18,720 --> 00:15:25,600
Misato: Why should anyone else love me anyway? I hate myself! [Maya] You're vulgar and impure. [Ritsuko] You're pathetic.

242
00:15:26,240 --> 00:15:30,860
Asuka: You're gross and disgusting! I've never seen anyone in such a disgusting relationship!

243
00:15:31,679 --> 00:15:34,700
Makoto: Congratulations on your promotion, Major Katsuragi.

244
00:15:35,840 --> 00:15:39,880
Misato: The me who is recognized is the me who's performing a role in order to be appreciated.

245
00:15:40,600 --> 00:15:41,720
Misato: But she's not the real me.

246
00:15:41,790 --> 00:15:43,880
Young Misato: Your true self is always crying, isn't she?

247
00:15:44,880 --> 00:15:46,700
Misato: Yes, but I am happy.

248
00:15:49,120 --> 00:15:49,920
Misato: I am happy.

249
00:15:51,980 --> 00:15:53,600
Misato: It's true, I am happy.

250
00:15:54,860 --> 00:15:57,440
Misato: I'm not! This isn't the happiness I want!

251
00:15:58,960 --> 00:16:00,920
Misato: This isn't me! It is not the true myself!

252
00:16:01,580 --> 00:16:03,420
Misato: I just don't want to face the harsh reality!

253
00:16:03,780 --> 00:16:06,300
Shinji: But we have to. We cannot live otherwise.

254
00:16:07,180 --> 00:16:08,940
Shinji: You know you'd be alone and afraid.

255
00:16:09,660 --> 00:16:10,220
Rei: Unstable.

256
00:16:10,700 --> 00:16:12,600
Ritsuko: If nobody was sleeping next to you.

257
00:16:12,880 --> 00:16:14,520
Asuka: Are you afraid of sleeping alone?

258
00:16:14,900 --> 00:16:17,840
Maya: Or does sleeping by yourself remind you of how empty your life is?

259
00:16:18,160 --> 00:16:20,580
Kaji: She can't stand not having other souls around her.

260
00:16:21,140 --> 00:16:23,000
Makoto: So, you'll sleep with anyone, won't you, Major?

261
00:16:23,180 --> 00:16:23,620
Misato: No!

262
00:16:25,080 --> 00:16:27,820
Misato: Yes, you just want to be infatuated with primal ecstasy.

263
00:16:28,440 --> 00:16:30,780
Misato: You want to fill the hole in your heart with temporary escape.

264
00:16:31,580 --> 00:16:34,280
Misato: You take advantage of men to soothe the pain in your soul.

265
00:16:34,840 --> 00:16:36,720
Misato: No! No! No!

266
00:16:41,880 --> 00:16:42,840
Asuka: Where am I?

267
00:16:44,480 --> 00:16:47,180
Shinji: This is the me which exists in your mind, Asuka.

268
00:16:47,360 --> 00:16:51,460
Asuka: And also, this is the me that exists in Shinji's mind at the same time.

269
00:16:53,980 --> 00:16:55,140
Shinji: What do you want, Asuka?

270
00:16:56,020 --> 00:16:57,520
Young Asuka: I want to live by myself!

271
00:16:58,120 --> 00:17:00,340
Young Asuka: I don't want my papa and my mama!

272
00:17:00,640 --> 00:17:02,080
Young Asuka: I'll live by myself!

273
00:17:02,740 --> 00:17:05,220
Young Asuka: And then, I won't cry anymore!

274
00:17:07,839 --> 00:17:09,560
Asuka: But I'm still crying!

275
00:17:09,880 --> 00:17:11,220
Asuka: Why am I crying?

276
00:17:12,079 --> 00:17:14,540
Asuka's Step Mom: I am sorry, I just don't like her.

277
00:17:15,079 --> 00:17:17,420
Mr. Langley: What happened to you, the able doctor?

278
00:17:18,000 --> 00:17:21,500
Rei: I told you, I'm a human being before a doctor

279
00:17:22,040 --> 00:17:24,060
Mr. Langley: But how can a trained person like you...

280
00:17:24,079 --> 00:17:27,900
Asuka's Step Mom: She acts too much like an adult, and she rejects me absolutely.

281
00:17:28,760 --> 00:17:30,780
Asuka's Step Mom: Sometimes she even scares me.

282
00:17:31,680 --> 00:17:33,100
Asuka's Step Mom: Have you had such a feeling with her?

283
00:17:33,860 --> 00:17:37,860
Mr. Langley: No, and in any case, you have now become Asuka's mother.

284
00:17:37,880 --> 00:17:40,320
Asuka's Step Mom: I'm your wife before that.

285
00:17:41,080 --> 00:17:42,620
Mr. Langley: Both duties are concurrent.

286
00:17:43,420 --> 00:17:45,640
Asuka's Step Mom: In a social perspective, yes.

287
00:17:46,540 --> 00:17:48,140
Asuka's Step Mom: But you can't quit being her father.

288
00:17:48,980 --> 00:17:51,340
Asuka's Step Mom: However, I can quit being her mother anytime.

289
00:17:52,220 --> 00:17:53,900
Mr. Langley: Hmph. You can say that.

290
00:17:57,320 --> 00:17:59,900
Young Asuka: No, Mama! Don't leave me!

291
00:18:00,340 --> 00:18:02,080
Young Asuka: I'll be good, promise!

292
00:18:02,980 --> 00:18:04,900
Young Asuka: Don't stop being my mother!

293
00:18:04,900 --> 00:18:06,900
Young Asuka: Don't ignore me!

294
00:18:07,440 --> 00:18:08,620
Young Asuka: No, Mama!

295
00:18:09,100 --> 00:18:10,680
Young Asuka: Don't kill me!

296
00:18:11,400 --> 00:18:12,980
Kyoko: Your papa hates your mama.

297
00:18:13,700 --> 00:18:15,100
Kyoko: He doesn't need me anymore.

298
00:18:16,080 --> 00:18:16,480
Kyoko: No.

299
00:18:17,080 --> 00:18:18,760
Kyoko: He didn't love me to begin with.

300
00:18:19,740 --> 00:18:20,860
Kyoko: But let's die together.

301
00:18:21,140 --> 00:18:23,100
Kyoko: Because he doesn't want us.

302
00:18:23,960 --> 00:18:25,300
Kyoko: He didn't need me at all.

303
00:18:25,960 --> 00:18:28,200
Kyoko: And he doesn't want you either, Husk.

304
00:18:28,240 --> 00:18:29,200
Young Asuka: I'm not wanted?

305
00:18:29,920 --> 00:18:31,400
Asuka: I'm not worth anything?

306
00:18:31,900 --> 00:18:35,120
Kyoko: Die with me, die with me.

307
00:18:35,220 --> 00:18:37,460
Young Asuka: No! I am not your doll!

308
00:18:37,820 --> 00:18:40,740
Young Asuka: I'll think by myself and live by myself!

309
00:18:41,600 --> 00:18:44,780
Asuka: And then, my mother was hanging from the ceiling.

310
00:18:46,220 --> 00:18:47,920
Asuka: She looked so happy.

311
00:18:49,580 --> 00:18:51,060
Asuka: But I hated how she looked.

312
00:18:52,160 --> 00:18:53,140
Asuka: I don't want to die.

313
00:18:54,000 --> 00:18:55,160
Asuka: I don't want to disappear.

314
00:18:56,460 --> 00:18:57,500
Asuka: I hate this!

315
00:18:58,340 --> 00:18:59,020
Asuka: I hate boys!

316
00:18:59,900 --> 00:19:04,360
Asuka: I hate my father and my mother. I hate everyone.

317
00:19:05,260 --> 00:19:08,400
Asuka: Nobody cares about me. Nobody stays with me.

318
00:19:10,480 --> 00:19:13,080
Asuka: So I don't want to depend on anybody.

319
00:19:13,860 --> 00:19:17,160
Asuka: But I hate it at the same time. It's a pain.

320
00:19:17,480 --> 00:19:21,340
Asuka: I don't want to be alone. I don't want to be alone.

321
00:19:21,420 --> 00:19:22,820
Asuka: I don't want to be alone.

322
00:19:24,720 --> 00:19:27,620
Shinji: Don't leave me. [Misato] Don't ignore me.

323
00:19:27,900 --> 00:19:29,160
Asuka: Don't kill me!

324
00:19:32,600 --> 00:19:33,580
Shinji: What the hell is this?

325
00:19:35,980 --> 00:19:38,680
Misato: This is the instrumentality which your father has initiated.

326
00:19:40,240 --> 00:19:40,800
Shinji: This is it?

327
00:19:41,280 --> 00:19:42,240
Misato: This is part of it.

328
00:19:43,220 --> 00:19:45,180
Asuka: You can't tell what the truth is, Shinji.

329
00:19:46,380 --> 00:19:50,720
Ritsuko: Truth is subjective. Therefore, you can barely tell that what you can feel is fact.

330
00:19:51,200 --> 00:19:52,420
Rei: The truth is within you.

331
00:19:53,320 --> 00:19:57,300
Fuyutsuki: And the facts that remain in your memory are what will become your truth.

332
00:19:57,820 --> 00:20:00,540
Ritsuko: Truth can be changed from time to time. Sometimes.

333
00:20:01,640 --> 00:20:04,600
Shinji: This is all fact. This is the result of everything?

334
00:20:05,180 --> 00:20:07,560
Asuka: This is real, but one of many realities.

335
00:20:08,520 --> 00:20:09,920
Misato: This is the conclusion you wanted.

336
00:20:10,760 --> 00:20:12,040
Shinji: Wanted? Me?

337
00:20:12,380 --> 00:20:13,900
Rei: Yes. Total destruction.

338
00:20:14,520 --> 00:20:17,060
Rei: You wished for a world in which nobody would be saved.

339
00:20:17,520 --> 00:20:21,120
Shinji: No! I didn't wish for this! The others didn't save me!

340
00:20:21,760 --> 00:20:23,380
Ritsuko: Nobody can save you from yourself.

341
00:20:23,780 --> 00:20:25,100
Kaji: This is what you wished for.

342
00:20:26,420 --> 00:20:29,300
Asuka: Destruction, death, and return to nothingness.

343
00:20:29,980 --> 00:20:30,960
Asuka: You wished for these.

344
00:20:31,800 --> 00:20:33,420
Misato: This is the reality that is.

345
00:20:34,120 --> 00:20:34,960
Shinji: What is reality?

346
00:20:35,480 --> 00:20:36,660
Rei: This is your world.

347
00:20:37,160 --> 00:20:38,900
Makoto: A world that exists solely for yourself.

348
00:20:39,640 --> 00:20:42,180
Makoto: One without time, space, or anyone else.

349
00:20:42,500 --> 00:20:46,040
Shigeru: A world in which every facet is determined by you.

350
00:20:46,980 --> 00:20:50,540
Maya: This is the world in which you just wait for others to give you something.

351
00:20:51,800 --> 00:20:54,480
Misato: This is your world unless you decide to change reality.

352
00:20:54,480 --> 00:20:57,480
Shinji: This is the world that is! Nothing can change that!

353
00:20:57,740 --> 00:20:59,800
Ritsuko: No. You yourself make the decision.

354
00:21:00,320 --> 00:21:03,400
Fuyutsuki: This is the world where your mind decides what will be.

355
00:21:06,100 --> 00:21:10,800
Misato: Whether it is the will to survive, [Asuka] or a wish for death, it is all up to you.

356
00:21:11,780 --> 00:21:16,780
Shinji: Are you saying that this darkness, this insane world, are what I really wish to create?

357
00:21:17,060 --> 00:21:17,400
Asuka: Yes.

358
00:21:18,060 --> 00:21:21,140
Kaji: You wished for a closed world that was comfortable for you.

359
00:21:21,480 --> 00:21:24,380
Makoto: You wished for it in order to protect you from your weakness.

360
00:21:25,240 --> 00:21:26,980
Shigeru: To protect your few pleasures.

361
00:21:27,800 --> 00:21:30,020
Rei: This is merely the result of your wish.

362
00:21:30,180 --> 00:21:34,660
Misato: In your closed world, in a world where only you are allowed to be, others cannot live with you.

363
00:21:35,520 --> 00:21:38,580
Asuka: But still you wished to close off the world that surrounded you.

364
00:21:39,520 --> 00:21:44,320
Ritsuko: Your wish ejected things you disliked and created an isolated and lonely world filled with nothing.

365
00:21:45,180 --> 00:21:47,500
Rei: This is the world your wishes have created.

366
00:21:48,120 --> 00:21:50,280
Rei: A private haven in the recesses of your mind.

367
00:21:50,980 --> 00:21:58,480
Asuka: This is how it all ends one of many possible endings. [Misato]This is an ending you brought upon yourself. You choose this fate

368
00:23:07,730 --> 00:23:09,580
Misato: An end always comes after a beginning.

369
00:23:10,010 --> 00:23:12,060
Misato: Will our hopes result in ultimate destruction?

370
00:23:12,580 --> 00:23:14,460
Misato: Is our whole existence death itself?

371
00:23:14,880 --> 00:23:19,580
Misato: It's our final episode, "The Beast That Shouted 'Ai' in the Heart of the World!"

372
00:23:20,480 --> 00:23:21,080
Misato: [music ends]

